<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="448" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1461]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,500,1255,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
The species is found on halophilic and mesophilic plants in marshes and swamps and is known to have a holarctic distribution from Eruope, Northern and Western Asia, 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1204,1293,1316]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1221,1304,1292,1317]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[163,1434,526,1392]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,519,1395]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Distribution maps of Aphrophoridae species in Iran: 20. Poophilus costalis. 21. Aphrophora salicina. 22. Aphrophora alni. 23. Paraphilaenus notatus. 24. Lepyronia coleoptrata. 25. Neophilaenus lineatus. 26. Neophilaenus campestris. 27. Mesoptylus iranicus. 28. Philaenus spumarius (grey dots are only based on the literature and the specimens were not examined). 29. Philaenus elbursianus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238928/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[1275,1304,1292,1317]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) to Eastern Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[218,375,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="Dlabola, J. (1957) Die Zikaden Afghanistans nach den Ergebnissen der von Herrn Klapperich in der Jahren 1952 - 1953 nach Afghanistan untemommenen Expedition. Mitteilungen Muncher Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 47, 265 - 303." type="journal article" year="1957">
Dlabola 
<number box="[316,375,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="1957.1964">1957</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[387,446,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="Dlabola, J. (1964) Ergebnisse der Albaniens - Expedition 1961 des Dt. Ent. Inst., 22: Auchenorrhyncha. Beitraege zur Entomologie, 14, 269 - 318." type="journal article" year="1964">1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<number box="[458,588,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="1967.1981">
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[458,517,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="Dlabola, J. (1967) Ergebnisse der I. mongolisch-tschechoslowakischen entomologisch-botanischen Expedition in der Mongolei, Nr. 3: Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha (Ergiinzung Acta entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 12, 51 - 102." type="journal article" year="1967">1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[529,588,1328,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="Dlabola, J. (1981) Ergebnisse der tschechoslovakisch-iranischen entomologischen Expeditionen nach dem Iran (Mit Angaben uber einige Sammelresultate in Anatolien) (1970 und 1973) (Homoptera, Auchenorrhycha). - II Teil. Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 40, 127 - 311." type="journal article" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nast" box="[601,721,1328,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="Nast, J. (1972) Palaearctic Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) An annotated check list. Polish Scientific Publishers, Warsaw, Poland, 550 pp." type="book" year="1972">
Nast 
<number box="[661,721,1328,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). As shown in fig. 
<number box="[937,967,1327,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="25.0">25</number>
, all locality records of the species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1391,1436,1328,1351]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">Iran</collectingCountry>
are in the northern 
<collectingCountry box="[369,414,1365,1388]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">Iran</collectingCountry>
except for one location in the south (
<collectingCountry box="[841,891,1364,1388]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">Fars</collectingCountry>
province), which has been recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="Dlabola, J. (1981) Ergebnisse der tschechoslovakisch-iranischen entomologischen Expeditionen nach dem Iran (Mit Angaben uber einige Sammelresultate in Anatolien) (1970 und 1973) (Homoptera, Auchenorrhycha). - II Teil. Acta Musei Nationalis Pragae, 40, 127 - 311." type="journal article" year="1981">
Dlabola (
<number box="[159,219,1400,1424]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The specimen was not available for the authors to examine. The species is considered as a potential vector for the bacterium 
<emphasis box="[350,498,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicName box="[350,493,1436,1461]" class="Gammaproteobacteria" family="Xanthomonadaceae" genus="Xylella" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Xanthomonadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="fastidiosa">X. fastidiosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which infests olive trees in Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="European" box="[907,1343,1436,1461]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" refString="European Food Safety Authority (2013) Statement of EFSA on host plants, entry and spread pathways and risk reduction options for Xylella fastidiosa Wells et al. EFSA Journal, 11 (11), 3468, 50 pp." type="book" year="2013">
European Food Safety Authority 
<number box="[1282,1343,1436,1460]" pageId="6" pageNumber="448" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
